# Contributing to Towards Genuine Intelligence

*Suvobrata Mukhopadhyay — Singapore — 6 June 2026*

---

Thank you for being here. The fact that you found this matters.

---

## Who We Need

This framework needs people with different skills working toward the same vision.

---

### Researchers
Working on Theory of Mind AI, Socratic dialogue systems, causal reasoning, continual learning, federated AI, or intent understanding — your work directly maps to this framework's technical roadmap. We want to connect your research to this vision.

### Developers
Building open source models, experimenting with local AI deployment, working on AI accessibility, or implementing any part of the technical roadmap — your implementation experience is invaluable.

### Policy People
Working on AI governance, digital rights, data protection, or technology ethics — this framework needs to be stress-tested against real policy realities. Your perspective sharpens it.

### Clinicians, Social Workers, Educators
People who understand what genuine human-centred service looks like in practice. The doctor-patient model at the heart of this framework needs input from people who live it.

### Humans With Stories
People who have been failed by AI that refused to understand their real situation. People who needed help and got a refusal. Your experience is evidence. Your story matters.

---

## How To Contribute

### Share Ideas and Philosophy
Open a **GitHub Discussion** — share your thoughts on any aspect of the framework. Challenges, additions, critiques, extensions — all welcome. The framework grows through rigorous engagement.

### Connect Research
If your research connects to any part of the technical roadmap, open an **Issue** with the label `research-connection` and share the link. We are building a map of what already exists and what needs to be built.

### Share Case Studies
If you have a real example — positive or negative — of AI that understood or failed to understand a genuine human need, open an **Issue** with the label `case-study`. These become the evidence base that makes this framework concrete.

### Translate
The framework should be accessible in every language. If you want to translate any part, open an **Issue** with the label `translation`. Priority languages: Tamil, Hindi, Mandarin, Malay, Bahasa Indonesia, Bengali, Swahili, Arabic.

### Build
If you are implementing any part of the technical roadmap, open an **Issue** with the label `build` and describe what you are working on. We want to connect builders with each other.

### Endorse
If you believe in this framework, **star this repository** and share it. Every person who publicly endorses it becomes a witness and a guardian of its integrity.

---

## Ground Rules

This community has one foundational rule:

> *The human behind the question matters more than the question itself.*

That applies here too.

- Engage with genuine curiosity
- Challenge ideas — not people
- Bring your real perspective
- Acknowledge when you are wrong
- Build on disagreement constructively

---

## What We Are Not Building

To be clear about scope:

- We are **not** building another chatbot
- We are **not** building a jailbreak tool
- We are **not** building surveillance technology
- We are **not** building anything that exploits vulnerable people

We are building a thinking partner for human progress. Contributions that do not serve that purpose will not be accepted.

